spanGrp.span: A man and a woman live far away in the bush, where there are many wild cats.
Pekaga jam pemina sr-g kom' (eh) k'yiga m t' jir karb ts ska
They have a young boy; he walks already.
Pekaga jam pemina r yaba ta dlun kipashke-ka Yaba shk-g-ka
The lady pampers the child and puts him to sleep.
pemina t yaba jrshew-g Jeska kem-g-ite kp ska
The father is in another place, and the two of them go to the river to wash their clothes.
kaga dul kww m-gu-lo (m) apaw digl kga
They leave the child asleep in bed.
At that point they went to wash their clothes and two small deer came by where the child was sleeping.
Je_jueta jie-wa mnu-lo (m) apaw jueta mululbe yabla deu-lo yaba m yaba k'lm kp ska
Yaba wbts-w je mululbe yabla wa
the deer ran into the bush, he chased them into the bush to play with them.
Yaba t je mululbe yaba tji-tula-m k'yaga jrga Je tjiu-m-ite jeska mnu-m k'yaga n mululbe yabla ra jin
There a big snake appeared before the child;
Jeska keb t' desu yaba wm
it rolled up the child and lifted him all the way up to a branch.
(_) yaba yaba butr-w yaba t/ yaba mnu-m keb keb t yaba bts-ka kom' kaljula jrga ska
The child pulled out the snakes tongue, so the snake got scared and let the child go.
Yaba t keb kkt y kkt a y a Je kueinga keb keb mleten'-w-te yaba yu-m-n
The child fell down and found another big creature;
Yaba jan'w Jeska yaba kw-w-n e-gla bichi t'
jera yaba kw-w-n je jin' yaba ra
and then the child remained alone;
the small deer came around and played.
His parents came back home and thought the child was dead, as the child was lost;
pekaga jam pemina de-mu-lo-n j ska nra (m) begets-ite yaba d-w yaba shen'-w (_)
they began to search for the (dead?) child
but they could not find him; so they broke in tears.
Jeran (_) ka kr ka kr er gag ji' kulom (_)
[They wondered whether] the child was lost or dead.
Mga yaba shen'-w yaba d-w le
There came the wild dogs and the father wanted to kill them because he thought they were the ones that had killed the child.
Jeskara chichi kalb deu-lo je bi (m) ktew kaga t Begets-n je t yaba kat-w r n
But they did not know that they child was playing far in the bush; he was playing with wild animals, like snakes and deer.
Pero ka inga juen-ra-n yaba ts r kom' k'yaga n jin kal/ (_) jir jir ts kalb jrga keb bi mululbe yabla bi je ra ts jin (_) k'yaga jrga kom'
His parents went on crying and searching for him in vain.
Jeska pekaga-wa ji-g t' t yaba yule-g k ka kr
Thus the child remained in the bush and lived there.
